# Debug logging when investigating bugs

**Policy:** When a user reports hard-to-reproduce behavior (black UI, stale state, wrong timing, platform-specific glitches), **add targeted diagnostic logs in the same workstream** — do not ask the user to set env vars just to see why something failed.

## Default: always-on failure logs

Log to **`stderr`** with the existing **`[rhino]`** prefix and a short area tag (e.g. **`[rhino] preview:`**, **`[rhino] dvd:`**, **`[rhino] ui:`** for buttons/keys/menus via **`user_action_log::act`**).

**Always print (no env var)** for:

- Early returns that explain missing UI or wrong behavior (`no plan`, `not ready`, `timeout`, `loadfile`/`seek`/`render` failure)
- Unexpected `None` / error branches the user would hit in normal use
- State transitions that invalidate caches (media change, entity switch, reset)

Use one line per event; include **observable inputs and outcomes** (paths, seconds, flags, mpv property snapshots when relevant).

```rust
// ✅ GOOD — visible on plain `cargo run`
eprintln!("[rhino] preview: pump timeout vo=false path={path}");

// ❌ BAD — user must discover RHINO_FOO=1
if std::env::var_os("RHINO_FOO").is_some() {
    eprintln!("...");
}
```

## Optional verbose trace

Env-gated **`log()`** is fine for high-volume per-tick/per-frame spam. Put it behind **`RHINO_<AREA>_DEBUG=1`** (or reuse an existing flag) **only after** always-on failure lines exist.

Pattern: small helper module per area (`preview_debug.rs`, `dvd_vob_log.rs`, `shell_debug_log.rs`) with:

- **`info(msg)`** / **`warn(msg)`** — always printed on plain `cargo run` (lifecycle + failures)
- **`log(msg)`** — verbose, env-gated only (`RHINO_<AREA>_DEBUG=1`)

## While debugging vs after the fix

- **During investigation:** add logs at decision points on the reported path; user runs **`cargo run`** and pastes `[rhino] …` lines.
- **After the root cause is fixed:** keep **always-on failure** logs that remain cheap and actionable; remove or env-gate noisy success/trace lines added only for the investigation.
- Document env-gated verbose flags in the feature **`## Notes`** when they exist.

## Do not

- Rely on env-only logging as the **only** signal for failures the user already sees.
- Log secrets, full file contents, or huge per-frame dumps without gating.
- Leave `println!` in library paths — use **`eprintln!`** or the area helper.

## Agent checklist (bug-fix / “still broken” turns)

- [ ] Failure paths on the reported scenario emit **`[rhino]`** lines on plain **`cargo run`**.
- [ ] Logs name **what was tried** and **why it stopped** (not just “error”).
- [ ] Verbose trace is optional; user can paste always-on lines without extra setup.
